# Email Functions

## Create Email Account

- Login to cPanel of your website
- Search the option of Email Accounts and click on it

```diagram

```

- You should see the next screen where the fields as Email , Password and quota field
- Provide your email account name , password and the size of the mailbox in Megabytes

```diagram

```

-  Click on Create Account to create email account

```diagram

```

- You can access your email accounts via webmail interface. 

## Manage Existing Email Accounts

- Login to the cPanel of your website
- Open Email Accounts
- You can see a list of existing email accounts. 
- From here you can change password, mail quota and delete an email account


```diagram

```

- To change Password click on Change Password. 
- Put your new password and then click Change Password.

```diagram

```


- To Modify mail quota click on Change Quota and click Delete to delete that selected email account

## Setup Email Forwards


- Log on to cPanel of your account
- Under Mail section click on Forwarders

```diagram

```

- The you will see list of forwarders currently active and button to add new forwarded. Click on Add Forwarder

```diagram

```

- On this interface you can set your desired email address you want the email sent to.  It can be forwarded to any email address that you use on daily basis e.g. your gmail account. 

```diagram

```


## Setup Auto Response

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Under Mail click on Auto Response

```diagram

```


- Then click on Add Auto Response button from the Auto Response page
- Now this is where you have to create the Auto respondes Once you have filled in the information, click on "Create/Modify:"

```diagram

```


## Enable SpamAssassin to stop the spam in my cpanel

- Log on to your website cPanel
- Under Mail section click on Spam Assassin 

```diagram

```

- Now on this interface as highlighted select "Enable Spam Assassin."  Once you have clicked this button, you will get a confirmation page.

```diagram

```

- Now on this interface set the strength . The recommended value for the strength is 5. Then click on Auto-Delete Spam


```diagram

```

- Click on Configure-Spamassassin to configure more setting with Spam Assassin. From there you can white/black list email accounts

```diagram

```

- Click Disable SpamAssassin to disable spam assassin on your website

```diagram

```


## How to Setup/Modify Mailing List 

- Login to your websites cpanel
- Under Mail section click on Mailing lists option

```diagram

```

- Enter the name and password in their respective fields. Select the domain -the mail list will be used on- from the Domain drop-down list menu. Then click on Add Mailing lists icon

```diagram

```

- Then you can see the your mailing list under current list

```diagram

```


- To change password Click on "Change Password " button next to the particular mailing list for which you want to change the password.
- On the next interface provide the new password and click on Change Password button

```diagram

```

- To edit mailing lists or add an email ID in mailing lists, then click on "Modify" button next to the particular mailing list that you would like to edit.
- Now log in to the list with your mailing list password. This will open up the Mailman Administration panel that you can use to adjust options such as adding a new email ID.

## Setup Remote Mail Server for Emails

- Log on to cPanel of your website
- Under Mail click on Mx Entry.

```diagram

```

- In the next interface scroll down. First, remove any current MX records that are in place

```diagram

```

- Then under the "Add New Record" section, enter 1 as the "Priority," enter your remote mail servers hostname as the "Destination," and then click "Add New Record."

```diagram

```

- For Google MX use the following settings.

```
1	ASPMX.L.GOOGLE.COM.
5	ALT1.ASPMX.L.GOOGLE.COM.
5	ALT2.ASPMX.L.GOOGLE.COM.
10	ASPMX2.GOOGLEMAIL.COM.
10	ASPMX3.GOOGLEMAIL.COM.
```

- After you have added all of your MX records, select "Automatically Detect Configuration" under the "Email Routing" section, and then click "Change."

```diagram

```
